label: Country
definition: Country in which study was conducted
codebookDescription: Country; Country wide

label: Study year
codebookDescription: Study Year; Country-wide

label: Village code
codebookDescription: A unique ID assigned to each study village. It represents the country code followed by a unique three digit number.

label: Village
codebookDescription: Village Name

label: Study arm
definition: Study arm that the study village was assigned to
codebookDescription: Study Arm
codebookValues: Abbreviations in arm descriptions: s= school based treatment, c= community wide treatment, h= drug holiday. Study arms describe treatment received by the village in each of the four study years. Arm 1= cccc, Arm 2= ccss,  Arm 3= cchh, Arm 4= ssss, Arm 5=sshh, Arm 6=shsh.

label: Participant ID
codebookDescription: Person ID

label: Sex
codebookDescription: Sex

label: Age
codebookDescription: Age (years)

label: Age group
codebookDescription: Generated based on age: 5_8= 5-8 years old, 9_12= 9 to 12 years old, 20_55= 20 to 55 years old, Other= not in above age groups

label: Schistosoma haematobium egg count, by microscopy
definition: Number of Schistosoma haematobium eggs counted, First filtration of the urine specimen, 'a' slide
codebookDescription: Number of Schistosoma haematobium eggs counted from the first filtration of the urine sample. In the variable name, sh= Schistosoma haematobium, 1 refers to the first (and only) urine specimen, and the letter refers to the first ('a') filtration.

label: Schistosoma haematobium egg count, by microscopy
definition: Number of Schistosoma haematobium eggs counted, First filtration of the urine specimen 'b' slide
codebookDescription: Number of Schistosoma haematobium eggs counted from the first filtration of the urine sample. In the variable name, sh= Schistosoma haematobium, 1 refers to the first (and only) urine specimen, and the letter refers to the second ('b') filtration.

label: Mean Schistosoma haematobium eggs per gram, by microscopy
codebookDescription: Mean Schistosoma haematobium eggs counted on the two filtrations of the urine sample

label: Schistosoma haematobium, by microscopy
definition: Presence or absence of Schistosoma haematobium infection
codebookDescription: Presence or absence of Schistosoma haematobium infection in this study participant, based on detection of at least one egg in the urine sample.

label: Urine volume (ml)
definition: Volume (in ml) of urine filtered in the first filtration
codebookDescription: Volume (in ml) of urine filtered in the first filtration

label: Urine volume (ml)
definition: Volume (in ml) of urine filtered in the second filtration
codebookDescription: Volume (in ml) of urine filtered in the second filtration

label: Number of school-age children in village
definition: Number of school-age children (SAC) in village
codebookDescription: Village level; # school-age children (SAC) in village

label: Number of school-age children treated in village
codebookDescription: Village level;# school-age children (SAC) treated

label: Percent school aged children treated in village
definition: Percent school-age children (SAC) treated in village. Calculated by dividing SAC_Rxed by Total_SAC
codebookDescription: Village level; school-age children (SAC) treated in village

label: Total population of village
codebookDescription: Village level; Total population of village

label: Total population treated in village
codebookDescription: Village level; Total population treated

label: Percent total population treated in village
definition: Percent total population treated in village. Calculated by dividing Total_Pop_Rxed by Total_Pop
codebookDescription: Village level; Percent total population treated in village

label: Longitude (degrees)
codebookDescription: Village level; GPS coordinates (latitude and longitude) of schools for each village

label: Latitude (degrees)
codebookDescription: Village level; GPS coordinates (latitude and longitude) of schools for each village

parentLabel: Eukaryote in urine detection aggregate data
